author: Ashley Walls
title: Tuesday’s prep soccer results
text:
Seattle Prep 8, Nathan Hale 1 
Mars Conn netted four goals and led the Panthers to a 3A Metro conference win over the Nathan Hale Raiders. Conn dominated in the second half, scoring in the 58th and 59th minutes. Mackenzie Floyd also knocked in a pair of goals and Helena Reischling recorded three assists.
Federal Way 2, Kentridge 1 
Brynn Ward had a goal and an assist to lead Federal Way over Kentridge in an SPSL 4A game. Rachel Kimura recorded the other goal for the Eagles.
Puyallup 5, Bethel 0 
Saige Lyons had a goal and three assists for Puyallup in a shut-out win over Bethel in SPSL 4A. Emily Estrada added a pair of goals and Jordyn Bartelson had two assists for the Vikings.
